name: Mew
flavorText: This Pokemon's body is covered by fine hairs that can be seen only under a microscope.
Attack1Text: Choose a type of Energy other than Colorless attached to Mew. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon of that type (including Benched Pokemon). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Pidgeot
flavorText: This Pokemon searches for food while flying at Mach 2. Its large claws make fearsome weapons.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Onix
flavorText: This Pokemon burrows through the earth at high speed, looking for food. The tunnels it digs are used by Diglett as nests.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Togepi
flavorText: This Pokemon is still immature. When threatened, it releases poison from its head and tries to drive its enemies away.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: A sure sign spring is on its way is when the seed on this Pokemon's back flowers.
Attack1Text: Each player flips a coin. Each player who gets heads chooses a total of 3 damage counters from among his or her Pokemon and removes them. (If the player's Pokemon have fewer total damage counters than that, he or she removes all of them.)

name: Raticate
flavorText: This Pokemon sometimes hunts for food in rivers, swimming using the small webs between the toes on its rear legs.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

name: Ledyba
flavorText: When it senses enemies approaching, this Pokemon releases an orange fluid from the joints in its legs and flees.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Ledyba.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: After lulling its enemies with its large eyes, this Pokemon sings them to sleep with a relaxing melody.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Butterfree
flavorText: The poison scales on its wings are waterproof, allowing this Pokemon to be active even on rainy days.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Butterfree. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: This Pokemon attacks its prey with its eighty toxin-producing tentacles.
Attack1Text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Water Energy attached to Tentacruel. For each heads, draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Marill
flavorText: This Pokemon's fur repels water like a duck's feathers, allowing it to stay dry and fluffy even in water.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Lapras
flavorText: This gentle Pokemon can understand human language and allows people to ride on its back.
Attack1Text: If Lapras has any damage counters on it, remove 2 of them from it (1 if it only has 1). If the Defending Pokemon has any damage counters on it, remove 2 of them from it (1 if it only has 1). The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: This Pokemon has a unique cry, as all three of its heads are always talking independently of one another.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Grass Energy attached to Exeggutor. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Slowking
flavorText: Its nonchalant reaction to everything somehow gives this Pokemon an imposing presence.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: When attacked, this Pokemon withdraws into its shell, although it can't quite pull in all of its long tail.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Wartortle but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: This Pokemon uses its six-foot tongue as if it were a hand. The origin of its anaesthetic properties is still a mystery.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 Pokemon (yours or your opponent's) with damage counters on it and remove 2 damage counters from it (1 if it only has 1).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: This Pokemon makes a loud jangling noise when it shakes its petals to spread poison powder.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from Vileplume (1 if it only has 1). Then, if you have any Benched Pokemon with damage counters on them, choose 1 of them and remove 2 damage counters from it (1 if it only has 1).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Primeape
flavorText: This Pokemon only calms down when there are no other animals or people aroundâ€”which means no one has ever seen it when it's not angry.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Primeape. Flip a coin. If tails, Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).
